## Triplex-Next Design System

Before modifying any component, read:
- `docs/ai/CONTEXT.md` — full context: stack, conventions, design tokens, workflow
- `src/components/{ComponentName}/{ComponentName}-AI.md` — component-specific docs

## Development conventions

- `docs/ai/codestyle.md` — TypeScript, React, LESS rules, DRY/KISS
- `docs/ai/tests.md` — unit, visual regression, e2e
- `docs/ai/stories-guide.md` — Storybook stories structure and checklist
- `docs/ai/commits.md` — commit format, branch naming, PR workflow

## Component workflow (adding a prop)

1. Update TypeScript interface in `{Component}.tsx`
2. Handle prop in render logic (use `clsx` for className merging)
3. Add LESS class in `styles/{Component}.module.less` or theme-specific file
4. Update Playground story in `stories/{Category}/{Component}.stories.tsx` (args + argTypes)
5. Add named story if prop has visual variants (Sizes, Themes, etc.)
6. Add/update unit test in `src/components/{Component}/__tests__/{Component}.test.tsx`
7. Update "История изменений" in `{Component}-AI.md`

## Non-negotiable rules

- `forwardRef` is mandatory on all components
- Never rename public enum values or prop names (breaking change)
- All items in `index.ts` barrel exports must remain exported
- LESS class names are accessed as `styles.className` (CSS Modules)
- Use `clsx` for conditional classNames, not string concatenation
- No hardcoded colors or sizes — use CSS variables from design tokens
- Design tokens follow pattern: `--triplex-next-{Component}-{Variant}_{Property}_{State}`

## Commit format

`TRIPLEX-XXX Short description` — every commit must start with the ticket number.
Branch: `TRIPLEX-XXX-short-description` (lowercase kebab-case).
